---
source: src/hooks/installer.rs
bead: bd-3usjw.7
surface: trauma_guard_hook_helper
assertion: ee hook preflight-shell --shell bash emits a deterministic, syntactically-valid bash snippet that wires ee preflight check into a DEBUG trap and blocks the upcoming command when severity is high|critical and the user declines the prompt
schema:
  envelope: ee.response.v1
  payload: ee.hooks.preflight_shell.v1
contracts:
  - snippet body is byte-identical across runs for the same (shell, ee_binary_path) pair
  - snippet embeds a single-quoted absolute ee binary path (no PATH lookup)
  - snippet installs `shopt -s extdebug` so DEBUG trap returning 1 actually blocks the next command
  - snippet declines safely when /dev/tty is unreadable (defaults to N, blocks)
  - snippet allows-listed shell-internal builtins (cd, set, unset, trap, exit, return, fc, history) bypass the trap
  - version field is the first 16 hex chars of blake3(snippet) for upgrade detection
  - severity_block enumerates the severities {high, critical} that trigger the prompt
evidence:
  - src/hooks/installer.rs::generate_preflight_shell_snippet
  - src/hooks/installer.rs::bash_preflight_snippet
  - tests/preflight_hook_bash.rs::bash_snippet_syntax_check_passes
  - tests/preflight_hook_bash.rs::bash_snippet_source_defines_hook_function_and_activation_flag
  - tests/preflight_hook_bash.rs::bash_snippet_blocks_destructive_command_when_prompt_defaults_to_no
  - tests/preflight_hook_bash.rs::bash_snippet_is_byte_stable_across_runs_for_pinned_binary_path
  - tests/preflight_hook_bash.rs::bash_snippet_carries_documented_contract_markers
